<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-07-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1173">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Wos y Gil</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Day</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Dominican Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">New
                                        York</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-07-19"><hi rend="italic">July 19,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to acknowledge receipt of your
                            communication of the 15th ultimo in reference to rules and suggestions
                            to neutral men-of-war entering or leaving blockaded ports.</p>
                        <p>I have taken due note and will communicate same to my Government as soon
                            as possible.</p>
                        <p>Please accept, sir, the renewed assurance of my high consideration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">A. W. y Gil</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Chargé d’Affaires.</hi></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>